{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place potatoes and water in mixing bowl then cook <strong><nobr>15 min\/100°C\/\/speed <\/nobr><\/strong>. Drain cooked potatoes through simmering basket.","Place drained potatoes, salt and cream in mixing bowl then mash <strong><nobr>30 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr><\/strong>. Transfer to a bowl, allow to cool for 20 minutes, then cover and refrigerate overnight.","Preheat oven to 200°C. Line a baking tray with baking paper and set aside.","Place reserved mashed potatoes, plain flour and baking powder in mixing bowl then knead <nobr>1 min\/<\/nobr>. Transfer to a floured surface, shape into a roll (approx. 24 cm) and cut into 8 pieces using a sharp knife. Dust each piece with flour and shape into balls. Using a rolling pin, roll each ball into a circle (Ø 10 cm). Arrange 4 flatbreads on prepared baking tray and bake for 20-25 minutes (200°C) or until golden. Repeat the baking process for the remaining 4 unbaked flatbreads. Serve warm or cold."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["500 g floury potatoes, peeled, cut in cubes (2 cm)","500 g water","½ tsp salt, plus extra to taste","50 g cream, min. 30% fat","150 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","1 tsp baking powder"]}],"id":"r143306","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-TnP96SFru28\/XZWYQj0kawI\/AAAAAAAAd7I\/j8CQV6uKTSgRpMAIjMvbM5MQhFgMHaWeQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_5RE8ATrTu01H9f22.png","title":"Potato Flatbreads","publishedAt":"2017-01-30T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4 g","fat":"2 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"28 g","calories":"648 kJ \/ 155 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray and paper, cooling rack, rolling pin, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["If you have 500 g leftover mashed potatoes you can make a quicker version of these flatbreads, starting at step 2.","Serve the potato flatbreads filled with cheese and ham as a snack or as a side dish for a meat curry or a stew.","The potato flatbreads make the perfect base for a filling and satisfying lunch."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","12h","8 pieces"]}